Section 16: Removing Spring Boot
    Lecture 84: Spring Security Configuration

1. Remove Spring boot security auto configuration
 1.1 Add Spring security property to change
    - src/main/resources/application.properties file
    - add "spring.autoconfigure.exclude[4]=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.security.SecurityAutoConfiguration"
      property in the application.properties file
    - add "spring.autoconfigure.exclude[5]=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.security.SecurityFilterAutoConfiguration"
          property in the application.properties file
    - add "spring.autoconfigure.exclude[6]=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.security.FallBackWebSecurityAutoConfiguration"
          property in the application.properties file
 1.2 Enable Spring Security
    - ej.springframework.config.SpringSecConfig
    - Add @EnableWebSecurity annotation on the SpringSecConfig class

2. setup core Spring security configuration
  - ej.springframework.config.SpringSecConfig
  2.1 Add @EnableWebSecurity annotation on the SpringSecConfig class to activate the Core Spring security

3. Test
  3.1 Start Server
  3.2 Open localhost:8080
  3.3 Check Displayed data (i.e, Product list and Product items ...)
  3.4 login and check weather still working application and the h2 testdb database (i.e, PRODUCT Table)
  3.5 Try to general user id and admin id